debrief.itemText: Please answer the following questions about your experience. Click and drag the red scrollbar to move down. Do not leave any box blank. Type ‘no’ or ‘n/a’ if you don’t have a response.
Briefly describe what you were asked to do in this experiment? (if there is existing text in the box delete it.
debrief.response: we were asked to choose between two answers, one of which would give us 10 points while the other gave one point. We had to pick the letter d if the number shown was below 153 and pick the letter f for numbers above that.We had to pick the letter j for anyletter closer to A and the letter k for any letter closer to Z. There was also a flashing shape right before we made our choice that determined whether we should pick the number task to do or the letter task.

debrief.itemText: Was there any part of the experiment that you found to be confusing?
Please explain anything you found confusing. (if No, type ‘No’)
debrief.response: Sometimes I found it hard to determine what the shape was telling me to do.
